There's really no substitute for natural sunlight when you're looking at fume in glass. Fume is the process of putting silver or gold into the flame, vaporizing it, and having it stick to the glass. The metals refract the light in different ways to create beautiful rainbows of color; if you know the secrets of fume. Thankfully I've had some amazing fume teachers including @jolexglass @royalsglass and @stresslessglass . You never stop learning though as long as you continue to experiment 🙃♥️✌️🚀. Stay Spacey Cadets!
